FBIS3-58396 "drweu008aa_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 January 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Italy's Ciampi, Andreatta Support Use of Force LD1101140794 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1200 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101140794 Rome RAI Due Television Network Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] NATO is ready to use force to break the sieges in Sarajevo, Tuzla, and Srebrenica. From Brussels, where the meeting of NATO memebers broke up a short time ago, a fresh warning was launched to the factions fighting in Bosnia. This time it seems that the alliance is serious in its intention. Francesco Mattioli reports from Brussels. [passage omitted] [Mattioli] The Italians present at the meeting, [Prime Minister] Ciampi and [Foreign Minister] Andreatta are in agreement with the other countries. [Begin Ciampi recording] I believe that the decisions made by the United Nations already leave open the possibility of air strikes. [end recording] [Begin Andreatta recording] It is unimaginable that the secretary of the United Nations would not authorize actions in defense of the troops. [end recording]
